## Project Overview
Rails 8 full-stack application built with the DARE methodology.
Server-rendered MVC (controllers + ERB views + Hotwire) with a layered domain.
Stack: ruby-rails-8 | Full-stack MVC | Layered Design | Hotwire | LLM integration | Action Cable

## Tech Stack
- Language: Ruby 3.3+
- Framework: Rails 8.0+ (Omakase, full app — NOT api-only)
- Views: ERB + Hotwire (Turbo + Stimulus), Propshaft asset pipeline, importmap
- Database: PostgreSQL 14+
- Real-time: Action Cable + Solid Cable
- Background: Solid Queue
- Cache: Solid Cache + Redis
- Deploy: Kamal

## Architecture (Layered Design)
- app/controllers/ — Thin controllers (HTTP only: render views / redirect, delegate to services)
- app/views/       — ERB templates + layouts (server-rendered HTML)
- app/helpers/     — View helpers (presentation logic only)
- app/handlers/    — Action handlers for JSON/API endpoints (RFC 7807 errors)
- app/services/    — Business logic (one class per operation, pure Ruby)
- app/repositories/ — Data access (interface + ActiveRecord implementation)
- app/models/      — Domain objects (no callbacks, no fat model)
- app/presenters/  — Serializers (Model → JSON for API responses)
- app/llm/         — LLM patterns (providers, prompts, validators, cache)
- app/channels/    — Real-time (Action Cable, authorized subscriptions)
- app/jobs/        — Background jobs (Solid Queue)

## Key Conventions
- Controllers NEVER call Repository or contain business logic
- HTML controllers render views; JSON/API endpoints return Problem Details on error
- Services are plain Ruby objects injected with dependencies
- Repositories abstract ActiveRecord; services never call AR directly
- JSON/API errors always formatted as RFC 7807 Problem Details

## Key Routes
- GET  /                       — Home page (server-rendered, home#index)
- GET  /up                     — Rails health check
- GET  /api-docs               — Swagger UI (rswag) for any JSON endpoints

